data_dir = "/kaggle/input/garbage-classification/Garbage classification/Garbage classification"

transform = transforms.Compose([
    transforms.Resize((224, 224)),
    transforms.ToTensor()
])

dataset = datasets.ImageFolder(data_dir, transform=transform)

train_size = int(0.7 * len(dataset))
val_size = len(dataset) - train_size

train_ds, val_ds = torch.utils.data.random_split(dataset, [train_size, val_size])

val_size = int(0.5 * len(val_ds))
test_size = len(val_ds) - val_size

val_ds, test_ds = torch.utils.data.random_split(val_ds, [val_size, test_size])

train_loader = DataLoader(train_ds, batch_size=32, shuffle=True)
val_loader = DataLoader(val_ds, batch_size=32)
test_loader = DataLoader(test_ds, batch_size=32)

classes = dataset.classes

def model_validate(model, loader, device=torch.device("cpu")):
    test_predicts = []
    test_labels = []

    model.eval()
    with torch.no_grad():
        for image, label in loader:
          image = image.to(device)
          label = label.to(device)
          output = model(image)
          predict = torch.argmax(output, dim=1)
          test_predicts.extend(predict.cpu().numpy())
          test_labels.extend(label.cpu().numpy())

    return f1_score(test_labels, test_predicts, average='macro')
In[]:
def train_model(model, optimizer, criterion, device=torch.device("cpu"), num_epoch=20):
    macro_f1_list = []

    for epoch in range(num_epoch):
        macro_f1_epoch = []
        loss_epoch = []
        val_predicts_epoch = []
        val_labels_epoch = []

        model.train()
        for image, label in train_loader:
            image = image.to(device)
            label = label.to(device)

            output = model(image)
            loss = criterion(output, label)
            loss_epoch.append(loss.item())

            optimizer.zero_grad()
            loss.backward()
            optimizer.step()

        macro_f1 = model_validate(model, val_loader, device=device)
        macro_f1_list.append(macro_f1)
        print(f'Epoch:{epoch}, Loss:{np.mean(loss_epoch):.4f}, Val macro F1: {macro_f1:.4f}')

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    plt.plot(np.arange(num_epoch), macro_f1_list)
    plt.xlabel('Epoch', fontsize=20)
    plt.ylabel('Val macro F1', fontsize=20)
    plt.show()

    return model, macro_f1_list

class ResNet(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, num_classes):
        super().__init__()
        self.model = models.resnet50(weights=None)
        in_features = self.model.fc.in_features
        self.model.fc = nn.Linear(in_features, num_classes)

    def forward(self, x):
        return self.model(x)

class ResNetPreTrained(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, num_classes):
        super().__init__()
        self.model = models.resnet50(weights=models.ResNet50_Weights.IMAGENET1K_V1)
        for param in self.model.parameters():
            param.requires_grad = False

        in_features = self.model.fc.in_features
        self.model.fc = nn.Linear(in_features, num_classes)

    def forward(self, x):
        return self.model(x)

models = [
    trained_resnet, trained_resnet_pretrain, trained_alexnet,
    trained_alexnet_pretrained, trained_mobilenet, trained_mobilenet_pretrain,
    trained_efficientnet_v2_s, trained_efficientnet_v2_s_pretrained,
]
name_models = [
    "trained_resnet", "trained_resnet_pretrain", "trained_alexnet",
    "trained_alexnet_pretrained", "trained_mobilenet", "trained_mobilenet_pretrain",
    "trained_efficientnet_v2_s", "trained_efficientnet_v2_s_pretrained",
]

f1_scores = []

for model in models:
    f1_val = model_validate(model, test_loader, device)
    f1_scores.append(f1_val)

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(17, 9))

ax.bar(name_models, f1_scores)
ax.set_ylabel('Models Macro F1-score')
ax.set_title('Macro F1-score')
ax.tick_params(axis='x', labelrotation=45)

plt.show()
